schemeContent.detailedDescription_md:
The scheme &amp;quot;Grant for Construction of Sports Infrastructure&amp;quot; by the Department of Sports, Government of Uttarakhand, aims to promote the development of sports infrastructure through financial support. Through this scheme, a grant of up to ₹50,00,000/- or 25% of the total project cost is provided for the construction of sports facilities such as badminton, table tennis, squash, indoor cricket, basketball, volleyball, football, hockey, and swimming. These facilities may also generate employment through operations.
&lt;br&gt;

<br>

The &amp;quot;Deployment of Prantiya Rakshak Dal (PRD) Volunteers&amp;quot; scheme was launched by the Department of Youth Welfare and Provincial Protection Corps. The scheme aims to provide financial security to PRD volunteers or their dependents in the event of death, disability, or injury sustained during duty. Under this scheme, PRD volunteers deployed to assist the police and serve in various government offices receive a daily honorarium. In cases of death, disability, or injury occurring during duty, financial assistance is provided to their legal dependents based on the nature and severity of the incident.
&lt;br&gt;

&lt;br&gt;

